  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "32c67acf-b32f-4efb-b4fa-ff9ff7db484a",
    "name": "Advanced API Features Project",
    "description": "Postman collection generated from the uploaded Express project.\n\nBase URL defaults to http://localhost:5010 because server.js starts Express on port 5010.\n\nRoutes found in code:\n- POST /auth/signup\n- POST /auth/login\n- GET /users\n- DELETE /users/:id\n\nNotes based on the current code:\n- /auth/login returns a JWT for a hardcoded super_admin user, provided JWT_SECRET is set.\n- /users requires Authorization: Bearer <token>.\n- DELETE /users/:id requires a token whose role is super_admin. The current login controller issues such a token.\n- signup does not persist to a database in the current code; it only returns the hashed user payload.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "11513518",
    "_collection_link": "https://go.postman.co/collection/11513518-32c67acf-b32f-4efb-b4fa-ff9ff7db484a?source=collection_link"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Signup",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Govind\",\n  \"email\": \"govind@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Password123\",\n  \"role\": \"user\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://localhost:5010/auth/signup",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": [
                "localhost"
              ],
              "port": "5010",
              "path": [
                "auth",
                "signup"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Creates a demo signup response. In the current code, this route validates required fields, hashes the password, and returns the user payload. It does not save to a database."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Login",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('Status code is 200', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "const jsonData = pm.response.json();",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Response contains token', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData.success).to.eql(true);",
                  "    pm.expect(jsonData.token).to.be.a('string');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "if (jsonData.token) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('token', jsonData.token);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "packages": {},
                "requests": {}
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"admin@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"Password123\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "http://localhost:5010/auth/login",
              "protocol": "http",
              "host": [
                "localhost"
              ],
              "port": "5010",
              "path": [
                "auth",
                "login"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Returns a JWT signed with process.env.JWT_SECRET. In the current code, credentials are not checked against a database; the controller issues a token for a hardcoded user id 123 and role super_admin."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
